'''Highway beautification''' is [[landscaping]] and control of the usage of the land by [[highway]]s.
In the [[United States]], highway beautification is subject the [[Highway Beautification Act]],<ref>[http://www.fhwa.dot.gov/infrastructure/beauty.htm Federal Highway Administration: "How the Highway Beautification Act Became a Law"]</ref> Section 131 of Title 23, [[United States Code]] (1965), commonly referred to as "Title I of the Highway Beautification Act of 1965, as Amended".<ref>[http://www.scenicflorida.org/law23usc131.html "Section 131 of Title 23, United States Code (1965)"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060616100108/http://www.scenicflorida.org/law23usc131.html |date=2006-06-16 }}</ref> The act placed restriction on [[billboard advertising]] along highways and removal or screening of [[Wreck yard|junkyards]].
