Sometimes the European part of {{flagcountry|TUR}} is considered part of the Balkan Peninsula. The [[Istanbul Atatürk Airport]] is located there. It had 63,727,448 passengers in 2017, placing it on the top spot in the list. The ( {{flagcountry|ROM}} ) Romanian airports that are considered to be on the Balkan Peninsula are [[Mihail Kogălniceanu International Airport]] in [[Constanța]] and [[Tulcea Airport]] in [[Tulcea]]. They have respectively 127,635 and 4,232 passenger traffic.

