{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Pleystor Glacier | other_name = | photo = Ant-pen-map-Liege.PNG | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Liège Island in the Antarctic Peninsula region | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Pleystor in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Palmer Archipelago]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|03|18|S|62|00|35|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|1|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|0.6|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Vapa Cove]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Pleystor Glacier''' ({{lang-bg|ледник Плейстор}}, ‘Lednik Pleystor’ \'led-nik 'pley-stor\) is the 2.2 km long and 1.2 km wide glacier on the west side of [[Brugmann Mountains]] on [[Liège Island]] in the [[Palmer Archipelago]], [[Antarctica]]. It is situated south-southwest of [[Zbelsurd Glacier]], draining the south slopes of [[Mishev Peak]], the southwest slopes of [[Pavlov Peak]] and the northwest slopes of [[Mount Vesalius]], and flowing west-northwestwards into [[Vapa Cove]].
The glacier is named after the [[Thracians|Thracian]] god Pleystor.
==Location== Pleystor Glacier is centred at {{coord|64|03|18|S|62|00|35|W|display=inline,title}}. British mapping in 1978 and 1980.
